JOHANNESBURG – Naspers’ subsidiary Media24 will pay a fine of almost R54-million for colluding on advertising discounts. The Competition Tribunal approved a settlement reached between the company and the Competition Commission. Media24 agreed to pay an administrative penalty of R13,8-million and will contribute R5-million to an empowerment development. READ: Media24 pays millions in cartel conduct settlement It will also give a 25 percent discount to small, black-owned advertising agencies, which will be capped at an annual fee of R35-million. The Media24 case is one of eight similar settlements between media companies and the commission. eNCA